en.value:
<p>In a certain code language, &#39;+&#39; represents &#39;&times;&#39;, &#39;&ndash;&#39; represents &#39;+&#39;, &#39;&times;&#39; represents &#39;&divide;&#39; and &#39;&divide;&#39; represents &#39;&ndash;&#39;. What is the answer to the following question?</p>

<p>11 + 50 &ndash; 150 &divide; 200 = ?</p>

hn.value:
<p>एक निश्चित कूट भाषा में, &#39;+&#39;, &#39;&times;&#39; को दर्शाता है, &#39;-&#39;, &#39;+&#39; को दर्शाता, &#39;&times;&#39; &#39;&divide;&#39; को और &#39;&divide;&#39;, &#39;-&#39; को दर्शाता है। निम्नलिखित प्रश्न का उत्तर क्या है?</p>
11 + 50 &ndash; 150 &divide; 200 = ?

te.value:
ఒక నిర్దిష్ట సంకేత భాషలో, '+' అనేది 'x' ని సూచిస్తుంది, '-' అనేది '+' ని సూచిస్తుంది, 'x' అనేది '÷' ని సూచిస్తుంది మరియు '÷' అనేది '-' ని సూచిస్తుంది. కింది ప్రశ్నకు సమాధానం ఏమిటి?

11 + 50 - 150 ÷ 200 = ?

mr.value:
एका विशिष्ट सांकेतिक भाषेत, '+' म्हणजे 'x', '-' म्हणजे '+', 'x' म्हणजे '÷' आणि '÷' म्हणजे '-'. तर खालील प्रश्नाचे उत्तर काय?

11 + 50 - 150 ÷ 200 = ?

bn.value:
একটি নির্দিষ্ট কোড ভাষায়, '+' মানে 'x', '-' মানে '+', 'x' মানে '÷' এবং '÷' মানে '-'. নিম্নলিখিত প্রশ্নের উত্তর কি?

11 + 50 - 150 ÷ 200 = ?

gu.value:
ચોક્કસ કોડ ભાષામાં, '+' એટલે 'x', '-' એટલે '+', 'x' એટલે '÷' અને '÷' એટલે '-'. નીચેના પ્રશ્નનો જવાબ શું છે?

11 + 50 - 150 ÷ 200 = ?

kn.value:
ಒಂದು ನಿರ್ದಿಷ್ಟ ಕೋಡ್ ಭಾಷೆಯಲ್ಲಿ, '+' ಎಂದರೆ 'x', '-' ಎಂದರೆ '+', 'x' ಎಂದರೆ '÷' ಮತ್ತು '÷' ಎಂದರೆ '-'. ಕೆಳಗಿನ ಪ್ರಶ್ನೆಗೆ ಉತ್ತರವೇನು?

11 + 50 - 150 ÷ 200 = ?

ta.value:
ஒரு குறிப்பிட்ட குறியீட்டு மொழியில், '+' என்பது 'x' ஐக் குறிக்கிறது, '-' என்பது '+' ஐக் குறிக்கிறது, 'x' என்பது '÷' ஐக் குறிக்கிறது மற்றும் '÷' என்பது '-' ஐக் குறிக்கிறது. பின்வரும் கேள்விக்கான பதில் என்ன?

11 + 50 - 150 ÷ 200 = ?

or.value:
ଏକ ନିର୍ଦ୍ଦିଷ୍ଟ କୋଡ୍ ଭାଷାରେ, '+' 'x' କୁ ଦର୍ଶାଏ, '-' '+' କୁ ଦର୍ଶାଏ, 'x' '÷' କୁ ଦର୍ଶାଏ ଏବଂ '÷' '-' କୁ ଦର୍ଶାଏ | ନିମ୍ନଲିଖିତ ପ୍ରଶ୍ନର ଉତ୍ତର କ'ଣ?

11 + 50 - 150 ÷ 200 = ?

<p dir="ltr">Cynicism​</p>

<p dir="ltr"><strong>In the following question, out of the four alternatives, select the word opposite in meaning to the word given.</strong></p>

<p dir="ltr">Befuddle</p>
Which of the following is a page related to chocolate?
en.comp:
A passage is given with 5 questions following it. Read the passage carefully and choose the best answer to each question out of the four alternatives.

But before I could be inspired by these amazing people, I had to cleanse my feed. I know my weaknesses: just last week, Facebook memories reminded me of a pizza party I'd had two years ago and I ended up ordering a chicken dominator, with garlic breadsticks and a jalapeno cheese dip. So much for Day One of Couch to 5K training. I stayed right on that couch. So far I've unfollowed Buzzfeed Tasty, TasteMade (even their adorable Tiny Kitchen) and several people who have the enviable advantage of being able to eat as much as they want and not put on weight. By my calculations, dark chocolate is healthy, so I'm still following Earth Loaf, Pascati and Mason & Co.

When I finally found a gym I liked, with the best trainers I have had, I unabashedly shared my workouts every day.
